00:00:02.602 --> 00:00:03.570 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>This is national,</i>

00:00:03.636 --> 00:00:05.271 line:5%,start
there's no more second chances.

00:00:05.338 --> 00:00:06.172 line:5%,start
This is it.

00:00:06.239 --> 00:00:07.540 line:5%,start
We need to learn a new group for team.

00:00:07.607 --> 00:00:09.776 line:5%,start
We have to do it today, and there's props.

00:00:09.843 --> 00:00:11.745 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Chloe Told me
that she wants to put dance.

00:00:11.811 --> 00:00:14.114 line:5%,start
ABBY: If she wants to quit,
I have a whole list of people

00:00:14.180 --> 00:00:15.348 line:5%,start
that want to take her spot.

00:00:15.415 --> 00:00:18.318 line:5%,start
KELLY: Maddie wins,
because she's with two choreographers

00:00:18.385 --> 00:00:20.520 line:5%,start
<i>who work with her seven days a week.</i>

00:00:20.587 --> 00:00:21.788 line:5%,start
I will do everything possible

00:00:21.855 --> 00:00:24.224 line:5%,start
for my daughter
to leave your studio next year.

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:27.227 line:5%,start
The top junior group winner

00:00:27.293 --> 00:00:31.264 line:5%,start
is by the Abby-Lee Dance Company!

00:00:31.331 --> 00:00:32.699 line:5%,start
We're going to Hollywood!

00:00:32.766 --> 00:00:34.534 line:5%,start
(squealing)

00:00:34.601 --> 00:00:36.269 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Here we are in Hollywood again.</i>

00:00:36.336 --> 00:00:38.905 line:5%,start
<i>The girls auditioning for the music video.</i>

00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:42.008 line:5%,start
<i>For all of my students,</i>
<i>this is the biggest opportunity</i>

00:00:42.075 --> 00:00:43.410 line:5%,start
<i>they have ever had in their career.</i>

00:00:43.476 --> 00:00:46.946 line:5%,start
I would say hip hop is the most difficult
of choreography to get.

00:00:47.013 --> 00:00:47.847 line:5%,start
Listen to me.

00:00:47.914 --> 00:00:49.382 line:5%,start
ABBY: You cannot act like this and cry,

00:00:49.449 --> 00:00:51.751 line:5%,start
because you become difficult to work with.

00:00:51.818 --> 00:00:55.055 line:5%,start
GIRL: I'm the one that always really
practices have to dance studio,

00:00:55.121 --> 00:00:56.222 line:5%,start
because it's a big deal.

00:00:56.289 --> 00:00:57.123 line:5%,start
I'm done!

00:00:57.190 --> 00:00:58.892 line:5%,start
HOLLY: Excuse me. Don't talk to me
that way. That's the first thing.

00:00:58.958 --> 00:00:59.793 line:5%,start
-I'm just saying--I'm done.
-Melissa.

00:01:01.828 --> 00:01:03.997 line:95%,end
(theme music playing)

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:05.498 line:95%,end
SINGER: <i>âª Get up âª</i>

00:01:05.565 --> 00:01:07.500 line:95%,end
<i>âª Get on the floor âª</i>

00:01:07.567 --> 00:01:10.470 line:95%,end
<i>âª My world is with my girls âª</i>

00:01:10.537 --> 00:01:12.872 line:95%,end
<i>âª Living on the dance floor âª</i>

00:01:13.540 --> 00:01:16.109 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:01:18.178 --> 00:01:19.379 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Ready, girls? Let's go.</i>

00:01:20.246 --> 00:01:21.214 line:95%,end
Come on in.

00:01:21.981 --> 00:01:24.717 line:95%,end
Well, you thought you were going home
after Lake Tahoe.

00:01:25.318 --> 00:01:27.554 line:95%,end
And here we are back in LA.

00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:29.722 line:95%,end
I have a big surprise. It's very exciting.

00:01:29.789 --> 00:01:33.326 line:95%,end
Before I get into that,
you notice there's no pyramid.

00:01:33.393 --> 00:01:34.227 line:95%,end
Yes?

00:01:34.294 --> 00:01:35.929 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:42.135 line:95%,end
ABBY: Everybody's in a straight line
because here in LA...

00:01:42.202 --> 00:01:43.503 line:95%,end
it's not really about the talent.

00:01:43.570 --> 00:01:44.838 line:95%,end
It's about the look.

00:01:44.904 --> 00:01:47.540 line:95%,end
<i>The girls have some hard lessons</i>
<i>to learn here in Hollywood.</i>

00:01:47.607 --> 00:01:51.077 line:5%,start
It doesn't matter how well you dance,
how well you sing,

00:01:51.144 --> 00:01:52.312 line:95%,end
how well you act.

00:01:52.378 --> 00:01:54.247 line:95%,end
If you're not the look that they need,

00:01:54.314 --> 00:01:57.050 line:95%,end
and you're not the package
that they're searching for,

00:01:57.117 --> 00:01:58.184 line:95%,end
you're not gonna get the job.

00:01:58.251 --> 00:02:01.654 line:95%,end
I'm ready to talk a little bit
about this surprise.

00:02:01.721 --> 00:02:03.256 line:95%,end
This is LA.

00:02:03.323 --> 00:02:06.960 line:95%,end
The best people in the world come here.

00:02:07.026 --> 00:02:09.195 line:95%,end
They're all vying for the same job.

00:02:09.262 --> 00:02:10.930 line:95%,end
Everybody wants to be a star.

00:02:12.532 --> 00:02:15.535 line:95%,end
You are going to get
the opportunity to audition

00:02:15.602 --> 00:02:17.971 line:95%,end
for a major music video.

00:02:18.037 --> 00:02:20.273 line:95%,end
(screaming)

00:02:20.340 --> 00:02:22.976 line:5%,start
MELISSA: In LA, I think this is,
like, the big deal

00:02:23.042 --> 00:02:25.211 line:95%,end
<i>that Maddie has a chance</i>
<i>to be in a music video.</i>

00:02:25.278 --> 00:02:27.247 line:95%,end
<i>She'll do great.</i>
<i>She really enjoys auditioning.</i>

00:02:27.313 --> 00:02:28.281 line:95%,end
<i>That's her thing.</i>

00:02:28.348 --> 00:02:29.716 line:95%,end
I don't know who's going to get it.

00:02:29.782 --> 00:02:31.084 line:95%,end
I don't know if all of you
are going to get it

00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:32.252 line:95%,end
or just some of you.

00:02:32.318 --> 00:02:33.720 line:95%,end
It's not up to me.

00:02:33.786 --> 00:02:35.255 line:95%,end
I don't make the decisions.

00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.590 line:95%,end
So it's every man for himself.

00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:39.759 line:95%,end
Tomorrow, instead of a rehearsal,

00:02:39.826 --> 00:02:41.427 line:95%,end
we will be having a class.

00:02:41.494 --> 00:02:42.962 line:95%,end
I'm going to teach a hip hop combination,

00:02:43.029 --> 00:02:44.998 line:95%,end
since that audition
is going to be in hip hop.

00:02:46.132 --> 00:02:48.868 line:95%,end
ABBY: This week is a whole new
ball game for the girls.

00:02:48.935 --> 00:02:50.670 line:95%,end
It's not a competition.

00:02:50.737 --> 00:02:52.105 line:95%,end
It's not about your costume.

00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:54.073 line:95%,end
It's not an awards ceremony.

00:02:54.140 --> 00:02:55.308 line:95%,end
That's all gone.

00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:57.844 line:95%,end
This is a real-life,
professional experience.

00:02:57.911 --> 00:02:58.978 line:95%,end
This is Hollywood.

00:02:59.045 --> 00:03:01.481 line:95%,end
They can chew up and spit you out,

00:03:01.548 --> 00:03:04.017 line:95%,end
or they can make all
your dreams come true.

00:03:04.083 --> 00:03:05.051 line:95%,end
It just depends.

00:03:05.118 --> 00:03:06.986 line:95%,end
You have to be in the right place
at the right time,

00:03:07.053 --> 00:03:10.023 line:95%,end
and you have to be prepared for the worst.

00:03:11.824 --> 00:03:15.195 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:03:15.261 --> 00:03:16.396 line:95%,end
ABBY: Okay!

00:03:16.462 --> 00:03:17.430 line:95%,end
Come on, back it up,

00:03:17.497 --> 00:03:20.300 line:95%,end
I have no idea
how this is going to go down tomorrow.

00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:21.768 line:95%,end
It could be a hip hop combination

00:03:21.834 --> 00:03:23.369 line:95%,end
just to see how quickly you pick up

00:03:23.436 --> 00:03:26.406 line:95%,end
because I would say hip hop
is the most difficult

00:03:26.472 --> 00:03:28.041 line:95%,end
of choreography to get.

00:03:28.107 --> 00:03:29.008 line:95%,end
<i>We tap.</i>

00:03:29.075 --> 00:03:30.910 line:95%,end
We do acrobatics, gymnastics, hip hop,

00:03:30.977 --> 00:03:32.912 line:95%,end
you know, ethnic dance, creative movement.

00:03:32.979 --> 00:03:34.147 line:95%,end
Whatever you need, we do it.

00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:37.951 line:95%,end
<i>But I would say</i>
<i>that hip hop was not their forte.</i>

00:03:38.017 --> 00:03:40.453 line:95%,end
And going up against all these kids
here in Hollywood

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:42.989 line:95%,end
to do hip hop five days a week--

00:03:43.056 --> 00:03:44.557 line:95%,end
we have our work cut out for us.

00:03:45.258 --> 00:03:46.826 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Aw, you're too funny.

00:03:46.893 --> 00:03:48.995 line:95%,end
-Only in a dream.
-Only in a dream.

00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:52.398 line:95%,end
Well-deserved, well-deserved.

00:03:52.465 --> 00:03:54.400 line:5%,start
Having the opportunity for my daughters

00:03:54.467 --> 00:03:56.903 line:5%,start
to try out for a music video is amazing.

00:03:56.970 --> 00:03:59.839 line:95%,end
I'm going to kind of take it
with what it is.

00:03:59.906 --> 00:04:01.975 line:95%,end
We'll go full-out. We'll do it.
We'll see what happens.

00:04:02.041 --> 00:04:03.710 line:95%,end
This is all very foreign to me.

00:04:03.776 --> 00:04:05.078 line:95%,end
I would imagine it's a time commitment,

00:04:05.144 --> 00:04:08.214 line:95%,end
whether you get the gig,
initially--all the running around.

00:04:08.281 --> 00:04:10.416 line:95%,end
-Right. I think that's the thing, is--
-With the auditioning,

00:04:10.483 --> 00:04:11.751 line:95%,end
because you don't just get it off the bat.

00:04:11.818 --> 00:04:14.120 line:95%,end
There's a lot of back work,
and that takes a lot of time.

00:04:14.187 --> 00:04:16.889 line:95%,end
And I worry about that for myself,
because I don't have that amount of time

00:04:16.956 --> 00:04:18.157 line:95%,end
because I have a school.

00:04:18.224 --> 00:04:20.627 line:95%,end
I have two boys.
I have a household to run.

00:04:20.693 --> 00:04:23.896 line:95%,end
I mean, I'm a housewife,
and that's good that I could just leave.

00:04:23.963 --> 00:04:26.332 line:95%,end
I mean, Maddie went to New York
seven times,

00:04:26.399 --> 00:04:27.900 line:95%,end
and they would call on a Tuesday.

00:04:27.967 --> 00:04:30.370 line:95%,end
Oh, we have somebody that
wants to see Maddie tomorrow.

00:04:30.436 --> 00:04:31.871 line:95%,end
And I'm like, oh, my gosh. You know?

00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:33.239 line:95%,end
Tomorrow, to go to New York.

00:04:33.306 --> 00:04:34.641 line:95%,end
Yeah. We thought we can't.

00:04:34.707 --> 00:04:36.809 line:95%,end
I can't sit here and say that
if an opportunity came along

00:04:36.876 --> 00:04:38.444 line:95%,end
for Nia that I would say...

00:04:38.511 --> 00:04:40.146 line:95%,end
-Oh, can't do that.
-...I can't do it,

00:04:40.213 --> 00:04:41.447 line:95%,end
because Nia wants this.

00:04:41.514 --> 00:04:42.949 line:95%,end
I think we've proved our mettle,

00:04:43.016 --> 00:04:44.617 line:95%,end
that we're willing
to put ourselves out there

00:04:44.684 --> 00:04:45.985 line:95%,end
and do what our kids need.

00:04:46.052 --> 00:04:46.886 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Whatever they need.

00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:49.489 line:95%,end
So if things come about, I'm sure that

00:04:49.555 --> 00:04:51.958 line:95%,end
if there's any group of women
that would make it happen,

00:04:52.025 --> 00:04:53.326 line:95%,end
-I think it's us.
-Oh, yeah.

00:04:53.393 --> 00:04:54.594 line:95%,end
And we would help each other, too--

00:04:54.661 --> 00:04:55.928 line:95%,end
-I mean, in a minute.
-WOMAN: Absolutely.

00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:58.931 line:95%,end
If we were going to an audition,
we would take your girls.


00:04:58.998 --> 00:05:01.267 line:95%,end
<i>Melissa is the master manipulator.</i>

00:05:01.334 --> 00:05:03.036 line:95%,end
I always say that she's calculated.

00:05:03.102 --> 00:05:06.472 line:95%,end
But she's always saying,
oh, I would do anything for the children.

00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:07.940 line:95%,end
You know what?

00:05:08.007 --> 00:05:09.942 line:95%,end
She would do anything for your children.

00:05:10.009 --> 00:05:11.644 line:95%,end
WOMAN: <i>Melissa knows how to play the game,</i>

00:05:11.711 --> 00:05:12.945 line:95%,end
and she's playing the game.

00:05:13.012 --> 00:05:15.014 line:95%,end
MELISSA: We all think
our kids are special...

00:05:15.081 --> 00:05:16.149 line:95%,end
-Of course we do.
-MELISSA: ...but LA?

00:05:16.215 --> 00:05:19.986 line:95%,end
-Everybody thinks their kids are special.
-MELISSA: LA? These kids are a lot.

00:05:20.053 --> 00:05:21.421 line:95%,end
There are amazing kids here.

00:05:21.487 --> 00:05:23.156 line:95%,end
I'm not worried about Maddie

00:05:23.222 --> 00:05:25.425 line:95%,end
<i>because she is the best all-round</i>
<i>dancer in the studio,</i>

00:05:25.491 --> 00:05:27.427 line:95%,end
and Maddie loves auditions.

00:05:27.493 --> 00:05:29.495 line:95%,end
<i>She's really excited,</i>
<i>and she'll do very well.</i>

00:05:30.797 --> 00:05:33.266 line:95%,end
Hit it. Hit it. Hit it.

00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:36.135 line:95%,end
Strut, two, three, four, draw plie.

00:05:37.303 --> 00:05:38.271 line:95%,end
Wow.

00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:39.205 line:95%,end
Got it?

00:05:39.639 --> 00:05:42.075 line:5%,start
Abby is funny-looking when
she tries to do hip hop.

00:05:42.675 --> 00:05:46.379 line:95%,end
Cross, chainee turn, bevel, kiss.

00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:48.381 line:95%,end
Girls, you need to be stronger.

00:05:48.448 --> 00:05:49.716 line:95%,end
Emphasize each movement.

00:05:49.782 --> 00:05:51.017 line:95%,end
It needs to be bigger.

00:05:51.084 --> 00:05:53.286 line:95%,end
That girl standing
next to you at that audition

00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:54.954 line:95%,end
could have already done 20 videos.

00:05:55.822 --> 00:05:56.956 line:95%,end
They know who she is.

00:05:57.023 --> 00:05:59.692 line:95%,end
MADDIE: <i>I'm kind of nervous</i>
<i>for that music video audition,</i>

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:01.527 line:95%,end
<i>but I'm also kind of excited.</i>

00:06:01.594 --> 00:06:05.898 line:5%,start
The bad part is, Abby told us
that it's going to be a hip hop audition.

00:06:05.965 --> 00:06:07.567 line:95%,end
And I'm not very good at hip hop.

00:06:10.436 --> 00:06:11.904 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>This is how an audition works.</i>

00:06:11.971 --> 00:06:15.007 line:95%,end
<i>You walk in, they throw</i>
<i>the choreography at you.</i>

00:06:15.074 --> 00:06:16.309 line:95%,end
You either get it, or you don't.

00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:18.211 line:95%,end
You have to be able to pull it off.

00:06:18.277 --> 00:06:20.179 line:95%,end
There's really no way to prepare for this

00:06:20.246 --> 00:06:23.649 line:95%,end
except by being an amazing dancer
in all genres of dance.

00:06:25.251 --> 00:06:26.552 line:95%,end
All right, next two.

00:06:26.619 --> 00:06:29.889 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:06:30.923 --> 00:06:31.991 line:95%,end
ABBY: Come on, girls.

00:06:32.792 --> 00:06:33.993 line:95%,end
Look, the dance studio's right there.

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:36.362 line:5%,start
See the letters, IDA? You can see it.

00:06:36.429 --> 00:06:37.463 line:95%,end
Come on. Hustle up.

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.599 line:95%,end
MSA is casting this video,

00:06:39.665 --> 00:06:42.402 line:95%,end
<i>so my girls have to go in front of MSA,</i>

00:06:42.468 --> 00:06:44.404 line:95%,end
a major dance agency

00:06:44.470 --> 00:06:47.140 line:95%,end
who rep some of the most prominent
dancers in our country.

00:06:47.206 --> 00:06:48.641 line:95%,end
SPEAKER: Squeeze on in, ladies.

00:06:50.209 --> 00:06:52.245 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>When we arrive</i>
<i>at the MSA audition,</i>

00:06:52.311 --> 00:06:53.546 line:5%,start
it's like a cattle call.

00:06:53.613 --> 00:06:57.116 line:95%,end
<i>There's tons of dancers,</i>
<i>little kids, teenagers.</i>

00:06:57.183 --> 00:06:58.418 line:95%,end
<i>There's parents everywhere.</i>

00:06:58.484 --> 00:07:00.353 line:95%,end
<i>You can kind of feel</i>
<i>that electric energy in the air.</i>

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:01.287 line:95%,end
<i>Everybody wants this.</i>

00:07:01.354 --> 00:07:04.557 line:95%,end
<i>Everybody who's here is here</i>
<i>for the same reason we are.</i>

00:07:04.624 --> 00:07:06.359 line:5%,start
As you all know, MSA represents

00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.594 line:5%,start
the top dancers and choreographers
in the business.

00:07:08.661 --> 00:07:09.996 line:95%,end
What we're doing here today is,

00:07:10.062 --> 00:07:12.298 line:95%,end
we're looking for our next
generation of stars.

00:07:12.365 --> 00:07:13.633 line:95%,end
So with that, please have fun,

00:07:13.699 --> 00:07:15.234 line:95%,end
and I look forward
to seeing you in the room.

00:07:15.301 --> 00:07:18.004 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:07:18.070 --> 00:07:20.573 line:95%,end
BEN: All right. So in an audition setting,

00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:22.308 line:95%,end
paying attention is key. All right?

00:07:22.375 --> 00:07:25.144 line:95%,end
We want to take our time
so you guys can get the combo well.

00:07:25.211 --> 00:07:28.214 line:5%,start
So your timing is one,
two, three, and four.

00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:30.516 line:5%,start
Five, six, seven, and eight.

00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:34.754 line:95%,end
(indistinct)

00:07:34.821 --> 00:07:38.224 line:95%,end
CHLOE: <i>We're having to learn</i>
<i>the combination really fast,</i>

00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:40.226 line:95%,end
and it's actually pretty long.

00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:43.663 line:95%,end
And then we have to go
and audition for the agents.

00:07:43.729 --> 00:07:45.531 line:95%,end
So that's a little nerve-wracking.

00:07:45.598 --> 00:07:46.532 line:95%,end
From the top--

00:07:46.599 --> 00:07:48.901 line:95%,end
five, six, seven, and eight.

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:51.571 line:95%,end
Go switch, drop, pull, switch, switch.

00:07:53.806 --> 00:07:55.575 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Usually, the way an audition works</i>

00:07:55.641 --> 00:07:57.243 line:95%,end
is, the girls learn the choreography

00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:58.377 line:95%,end
in big, huge groups.

00:07:58.444 --> 00:08:00.313 line:95%,end
You could take 100 kids in at a time.

00:08:00.379 --> 00:08:02.081 line:95%,end
Then they start to cut,

00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:05.418 line:95%,end
and they break it down into smaller groups
to actually go in and audition.

00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:08.554 line:95%,end
(indistinct chatter)

00:08:08.621 --> 00:08:10.456 line:95%,end
BEN: Music. Let's give it a go.

00:08:10.523 --> 00:08:11.891 line:95%,end
-You all right back here?
-No.

00:08:11.958 --> 00:08:13.860 line:95%,end
-What's wrong?
-I don't know it.

00:08:13.926 --> 00:08:15.161 line:95%,end
BEN: You don't know it? That's okay.

00:08:15.228 --> 00:08:16.929 line:95%,end
Do as much as you can. Okay?

