Good.

00:19:14.419 --> 00:19:16.221 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: <i>For the music video,</i>
<i>they're looking for someone</i>

00:19:16.288 --> 00:19:19.691 line:5%,start
<i>who can really act, somebody</i>
<i>who's really going to be, you know,</i>

00:19:19.758 --> 00:19:22.427 line:5%,start
<i>animated and believable on camera.</i>

00:19:22.494 --> 00:19:24.196 line:5%,start
<i>So I set up a meeting for Chloe</i>

00:19:24.263 --> 00:19:27.166 line:5%,start
<i>with one of the best acting coaches</i>
<i>in LA, Howard Fine.</i>

00:19:27.232 --> 00:19:29.801 line:95%,end
HOWARD: If your goal
is really to be an actress,

00:19:29.868 --> 00:19:31.470 line:95%,end
you have to have this open heart.

00:19:31.537 --> 00:19:34.339 line:95%,end
So we're going to explore
a little bit emotional recall.

00:19:34.406 --> 00:19:37.009 line:95%,end
Can you remember
the saddest day of your life,

00:19:37.075 --> 00:19:38.443 line:95%,end
what that would be?

00:19:39.511 --> 00:19:42.848 line:95%,end
I think when my great-grandfather died

00:19:42.915 --> 00:19:45.150 line:95%,end
because I had a very good
relationship with him.

00:19:45.217 --> 00:19:47.419 line:95%,end
-HOWARD: Do you remember that day?
-CHLOE: Mm-hmm.

00:19:47.486 --> 00:19:48.520 line:95%,end
HOWARD: Tell me about it.

00:19:50.956 --> 00:19:53.825 line:95%,end
I know my mind
was kind of just blank there.

00:19:55.727 --> 00:19:57.796 line:5%,start
I'm having a hard time getting emotional,

00:19:57.863 --> 00:20:00.966 line:5%,start
and I'm having a hard time
expressing myself to him.

00:20:01.033 --> 00:20:03.602 line:95%,end
So as an actress,
this is what it's all about--

00:20:03.669 --> 00:20:05.904 line:95%,end
contacting real sources.

00:20:06.672 --> 00:20:08.774 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>He really made her</i>
<i>look inside herself,</i>

00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:10.642 line:95%,end
<i>and it became very introspective.</i>

00:20:10.709 --> 00:20:13.412 line:95%,end
And I don't think
that's what Chloe envisioned

00:20:13.478 --> 00:20:15.113 line:95%,end
an acting class to be like.

00:20:16.114 --> 00:20:18.650 line:95%,end
HOWARD: Do you consider yourself
the number one dancer in the company?

00:20:19.718 --> 00:20:22.654 line:95%,end
There's another girl that's pretty good.

00:20:22.721 --> 00:20:23.655 line:95%,end
Her name is Maddie.

00:20:23.722 --> 00:20:28.227 line:95%,end
I think we're maybe
the better ones in the group.

00:20:28.293 --> 00:20:32.064 line:95%,end
Good. What stops you
from going for number one?


00:20:33.098 --> 00:20:34.733 line:95%,end
Nothing, I guess.

00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:36.101 line:95%,end
-What's that?
-Nothing.

00:20:36.168 --> 00:20:38.737 line:95%,end
HOWARD: Nothing stops you
from going for number one.

00:20:38.804 --> 00:20:40.706 line:95%,end
I have a feeling you stop yourself.

00:20:42.474 --> 00:20:44.710 line:95%,end
And it could be because
you're such a sensitive little girl

00:20:44.776 --> 00:20:46.979 line:95%,end
that you think about how
the others might be hurt.

00:20:47.613 --> 00:20:49.047 line:95%,end
-Does that make sense?
-Yes.

00:20:49.114 --> 00:20:52.517 line:95%,end
HOWARD: Okay, you have to understand that
your success doesn't hurt anybody else.

00:20:52.584 --> 00:20:54.553 line:95%,end
CHLOE: Mr. Fine said,
when I walk in there,

00:20:54.620 --> 00:20:57.256 line:95%,end
pretend like I already have
the lead character

00:20:57.322 --> 00:20:58.590 line:95%,end
and be really confident.

00:20:58.657 --> 00:21:01.660 line:95%,end
HOWARD: So, Chloe, I want you
not to be afraid,

00:21:01.727 --> 00:21:04.463 line:95%,end
to be strong.

00:21:04.529 --> 00:21:08.834 line:95%,end
You have to stop beating yourself up
and doubting yourself.

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:11.069 line:95%,end
Chloe has really been struggling
with her confidence lately,

00:21:11.136 --> 00:21:13.639 line:95%,end
and personally, I think it has a lot to do
with Abby constantly

00:21:13.705 --> 00:21:15.474 line:95%,end
yelling at her and berating her.

00:21:15.540 --> 00:21:17.876 line:95%,end
I think if she could get comfortable
in her own skin,

00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:19.411 line:95%,end
she could totally pull this off.

00:21:19.478 --> 00:21:20.345 line:95%,end
Absolutely.

00:21:20.412 --> 00:21:21.346 line:95%,end
-All right
-Thank you.

00:21:21.413 --> 00:21:23.548 line:95%,end
-Bye-bye, thank you so much.
-Thank you.

00:21:23.615 --> 00:21:26.618 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:29.087 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>When the girls are busy rehearsing,</i>

00:21:29.154 --> 00:21:32.257 line:95%,end
<i>it's an opportunity for us moms</i>
<i>to get out and see the town.</i>

00:21:32.324 --> 00:21:34.860 line:5%,start
I feel bad for the girls
because us moms are always out

00:21:34.926 --> 00:21:36.428 line:5%,start
having fun while they're busy rehearsing.

00:21:36.495 --> 00:21:38.964 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I'm just excited that our girls
are finally getting to do something

00:21:39.031 --> 00:21:41.633 line:95%,end
that Abby doesn't determine
who the star is.

00:21:42.434 --> 00:21:45.704 line:95%,end
I am, and I mean,
I'm not going to beat around the bush.

00:21:45.771 --> 00:21:47.773 line:95%,end
I think all of us are sitting here
hoping it's our kids

00:21:47.839 --> 00:21:50.242 line:95%,end
because they're so used to Abby
being the way she is.

00:21:50.309 --> 00:21:51.843 line:95%,end
WOMAN: I guarantee you, it'll be mine.

00:21:52.911 --> 00:21:56.448 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I actually went out to coffee
with Seven the other day.

00:21:59.951 --> 00:22:01.486 line:95%,end
-Oh, did you?
-MELISSA: Mm-hmm.

00:22:01.553 --> 00:22:02.387 line:95%,end
Oh!

00:22:02.454 --> 00:22:05.557 line:95%,end
KELLY: So I'm assuming
since you met with him for lunch--

00:22:05.624 --> 00:22:07.292 line:95%,end
-is Maddie the star?
-No.

00:22:07.359 --> 00:22:08.694 line:95%,end
No, no, no. Not at all.

00:22:08.760 --> 00:22:10.162 line:95%,end
That's not playing by the rules.

00:22:10.228 --> 00:22:11.763 line:95%,end
I would never think
to go with the producer

00:22:11.830 --> 00:22:13.699 line:95%,end
because I think of playing by the rules.

00:22:13.765 --> 00:22:15.734 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Playing by the rules?
Why is that not playing by the rules?

00:22:15.801 --> 00:22:18.737 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Because it's going above
and beyond what the rest of us do.

00:22:20.272 --> 00:22:21.106 line:95%,end
I don't think that at all.

00:22:21.173 --> 00:22:23.208 line:95%,end
<i>Of course Melissa met</i>
<i>with the producer Seven.</i>

00:22:23.275 --> 00:22:24.710 line:5%,start
It's Maddie we're talking about.

00:22:24.776 --> 00:22:27.145 line:5%,start
She would do anything
to make sure Maddie got the starring role.

00:22:27.212 --> 00:22:28.947 line:95%,end
You have an advantage over us.

00:22:29.815 --> 00:22:31.650 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Christi says
I don't play by the rules.

00:22:31.717 --> 00:22:33.085 line:5%,start
What rules? This is Hollywood.

00:22:33.151 --> 00:22:34.586 line:5%,start
This isn't Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:22:34.653 --> 00:22:35.687 line:95%,end
<i>I'll do whatever I want.</i>

00:22:35.754 --> 00:22:36.621 line:95%,end
<i>I don't answer to her.</i>

00:22:36.688 --> 00:22:39.124 line:95%,end
KELLY: I don't know.
That's why Maddie gets ahead.

00:22:40.258 --> 00:22:42.394 line:95%,end
And I'm really naive, because I think
if you just go to an audition,

00:22:42.461 --> 00:22:44.129 line:95%,end
you get (indistinct)
based on your audition.

00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:47.065 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>Once again,</i>
<i>it's not an even playing field.</i>

00:22:47.132 --> 00:22:49.101 line:95%,end
This is what we've been dealing
with all season.

00:22:49.167 --> 00:22:51.737 line:95%,end
And frankly, this is what
we've been dealing with for years.

00:22:51.803 --> 00:22:54.106 line:95%,end
So, you know, I went into this thinking

00:22:54.172 --> 00:22:56.375 line:95%,end
that my daughter had at least a chance.

00:22:56.441 --> 00:22:58.910 line:95%,end
And at this point,
of course she doesn't have a chance.

00:22:58.977 --> 00:23:02.381 line:95%,end
I didn't take the director out
for, you know, cocktails, so.

00:23:02.447 --> 00:23:03.882 line:95%,end
HOLLY: And those connections
involving relationships.

